  <refnamediv>
    <refname>DH_size, DH_bits</refname>
<refpurpose>get Diffie-Hellman prime size</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis format="linespecific">#include &lt;openssl/dh.h&gt;</synopsis>
<synopsis format="linespecific">int DH_size(const DH *dh);</synopsis>
<synopsis format="linespecific">int DH_bits(const DH *dh);</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection xml:id="sources.openssl.doc.crypto.DH_size.pod:DESCRIPTION"><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      DH_size() returns the Diffie-Hellman prime size in bytes. It can be
      used to determine how much memory must be allocated for the shared
      secret computed by DH_compute_key().
    </para>
    <para>
      DH_bits() returns the number of significant bits.
    </para>
    <para>
      <emphasis role="bold">dh</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold">dh-&gt;p</emphasis> must not be <emphasis role="bold">NULL</emphasis>.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection xml:id="sources.openssl.doc.crypto.DH_size.pod:RETURN_VALUE"><title>RETURN VALUE</title>
    <para>
      The size.
    </para>
  </refsection>
